\[ \text{Percent Growth} = \left( \frac{\text{Final Value} - \text{Initial Value}}{\text{Initial Value}} \right) \times 100 \]

For engaged users, the same formula applies.

**Average Session Duration Growth**:
\[ = \left( \frac{20.5 - 22.33}{22.33} \right) \times 100 \approx -8.19\% \]

**Engaged Users Growth**:
\[ = \left( \frac{5 - 4}{4} \right) \times 100 = 25\% \]

Since the percent growth of engaged users (25%) is greater than the change in average session duration (-8.19%), we will plot both lines since Monday.
